cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MM, cs.NE 

This paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category as it deals with medical image analysis and segmentation. The use of an end-to-end network and the extraction of global features also suggests that it could belong to the machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. The involvement of 3D geometric information and volumetric segmentation could also place it in the multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category. Finally, the use of a progressive fusion network and the focus on achieving state-of-the-art performance suggests that it could belong to the neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE) sub-category.
